This project use astro, react, shadcn, framer-motion to build the Spark Lab offical website.

## Rules
- use pnpm not npm, eg: `pnpm i react`
- Use Astro for the outermost layer, but write the core page components using React. The Astro part should not contain any UI code.
- If use motion in react component, use the following method to get the translations:

```typescript
import { useI18n } from "@/hooks/useI18n";

const Demo = () => {
  const { t } = useI18n();
  ...
}
```
- If a CSR component, do not use astro to pass parameters.

Bad Case:
```astro
<B3 t={t} client:visible />
```
Reason: This will cause the component to be rendered on the server side, which is not what we want.

Good Case:
```astro
<B3 client:only="react" />

export const B3 = () => {
  const { t } = useI18n();
  ...
}
```



## Other

- frmaer-motion now named `motion`, use 

```typescript
import {
  useMotionValueEvent,
  useScroll,
  useTransform,
  motion,
} from "motion/react";
```

to import the motion module.